# One Cred — build-time secrets (open source friendly).
#
# Copy this file to ".env" and customize. `.env` is git-ignored.
# Values are baked into the binary at build/run time via
# `--dart-define-from-file=.env`. They never appear in the bundled assets.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# APP_PEPPER
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# An optional extra secret mixed into the key-derivation step before
# encrypting/decrypting your exported .vault files.
#
# How it works:
#   passphrase_key  = PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256(passphrase || APP_PEPPER, salt)
#
# Why you want one:
#   * Even if someone steals your .vault export and tries to brute-force
#     it, they also need the pepper baked into YOUR build of the app.
#   * Different installs with different peppers produce INCOMPATIBLE
#     .vault files — switching pepper invalidates old exports.
#
# Leave empty for an OSS default build (no pepper). For personal use,
# generate one with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
APP_PEPPER=
